    <title>🇵🇱 Getting Started with Machine Learning using SAP HANA (Wrocław, PL)</title>
    <updated>2024-10-15T13:37:20.895000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Vitaliy-R</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/183</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;TABLE border="1" width="100%"&gt;&lt;TBODY&gt;&lt;TR&gt;&lt;TD width="100%"&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color="#FF0000"&gt;The&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color="#FF0000"&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;binding registration for this&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color="#FF0000"&gt;SAP CodeJam is at:&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://career.leverx.com/external-events/sap-codejam" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://career.leverx.com/external-events/sap-codejam&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/TD&gt;&lt;/TR&gt;&lt;/TBODY&gt;&lt;/TABLE&gt;&lt;P&gt;This&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;A href="https://groups.community.sap.com/t5/sap-codejam/gh-p/code-jam" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;SAP CodeJam&lt;/A&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;event is on the topic of&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Getting&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;Started with Machine Learning using SAP HANA&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;and Python&lt;/SPAN&gt;. You do not need to have any background in the topic, but a lot of curiosity!&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;You'll become acquainted with how embedded Machine Learning in SAP HANA can be used to build ML models. In working through this CodeJam you'll also become familiar with how the SAP Business Application Studio can be used to work with Jupyter notebooks.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;This is a&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;free&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;in-person event&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;and is planned for&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Wednesday, October 30th&amp;nbsp;&lt;/STRONG&gt;in&lt;STRONG&gt; Wrocław, Poland &lt;span class="lia-unicode-emoji" title=":poland:"&gt;🇵🇱&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;from 10:00 to 16:00 CEST (UTC+2)&lt;/SPAN&gt;.&amp;nbsp;The language of the event and the content will be in English.&amp;nbsp;The instructor is a&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;A href="https://developers.sap.com/developer-advocates.html" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;Developer Advocate&lt;/A&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;STRONG&gt;Vitaliy Rudnytskiy&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Every attendee must complete essential prerequisites&lt;STRONG&gt; before arriving at the event location&lt;/STRONG&gt;. They are documented here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://github.com/SAP-samples/hana-ml-py-codejam/blob/main/prerequisites.md#prerequisites" target="_self" rel="nofollow noreferrer noopener"&gt;https://github.com/SAP-samples/hana-ml-py-codejam/blob/main/prerequisites.md&lt;/A&gt;.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P data-unlink="true"&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;The event is being&lt;SPAN class=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;hosted by LeverX&amp;nbsp;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN class=""&gt;at&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;FONT size="2"&gt;LABO | Coworking&lt;BR /&gt;Grodzka 9, 50-137 Wrocław&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Note that spaces are limited and you must register via &lt;A href="https://career.leverx.com/external-events/sap-codejam" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://career.leverx.com/external-events/sap-codejam&lt;/A&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Visit the SAP&lt;A href="https://groups.community.sap.com/t5/sap-codejam/gh-p/code-jam" target="_self" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;&amp;nbsp;CodeJam group&lt;/A&gt; for more information on SAP CodeJam events, to ask questions, and to chat with your fellow attendees.&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/sap-codejam/getting-started-with-machine-learning-using-sap-hana-wroc%C5%82aw-pl/ev-p/13899542"/>
    <published>2024-10-15T13:37:20.895000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
